sources.title: Francis the First (1937 History) with Fernandel, Mona Goya | by Christian-Jaque | french film
sources.description:
Honorin, a timid stage manager with dreams of playing a cavalier, is hypnotized to calm his stage fright but instead finds himself transported to the Renaissance court of Francis I. There, he navigates royal intrigue, duels, and accusations of witchcraft while hilariously blending modern knowledge with medieval chaos.

Original title: François Premier (1937)

Director: Christian-Jaque
Writer: Paul Fékété
Stars: Fernandel, Mona Goya, Alexandre Rignault
Genres: French Cinema, Comedy, Fantasy, History
